Ecological notes : very common in broad-leaved and carr woodland; also found in mixed woodland; parkland with ancient oaks; ancient woodland with oak, hazel and bramble; wooded lake margin; wet and dry heathland; wetlands including fen, sedge bed and water meadows; grassland with pingo pools; grounds of horticultural research station; school grounds with old poplars; gardens; in houses; pest on mushroom farms, in rubbish.
